Germany Debates Scrapping Nuclear Tax in Energy Shift, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 
2011-05-03T06:11:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/germany-debates-scrapping-nuclear-tax-in-energy-shift-handelsblatt-says.html
German Chancellor  Angela Merkel 
discussed scrapping a tax on nuclear fuel rods with government
colleagues as she seeks to accelerate the country’s exit from
atomic energy, Handelsblatt reported.  While Merkel favors setting a date for the phase-out,
Germany could also employ a system that fixes volumes reactors
are allowed to generate before being switched off, the newspaper
said, citing unidentified people close to the government  Federal and state government officials will discuss the
exit tomorrow and Economy MinisterRainer Bruederle will meet
state premiers on May 10, Handelsblatt reported. Merkel hasn’t
yet set a date for a meeting with the country’s biggest energy
companies, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Comfort at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net  